{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_goldman_ver01/data/sn82015313/0038334928A/1930082901/0072.xml":{"full_text":"PAGE 18\nAdvocates of\nWright\u2019s Beauty Shop\nExpert Beauticians\nNestle Circuline Permanents\n$5\nAlso Mid-Summer Special, $2.50\n108 Mass. Ave. LI 0088\nOpen Evenings\nHENRY SEPTIC TANK CO.\n545 Warren Avenue\nBElmont 0545\nHOOVER ACTION\nSPORS HOPE OF\nTARIFF RELIEF\nNaming of Thomas W.\nPage to Board Is Hailed\nas Good Move.\nBu Srrtppt-Howard. Newspaper Alliance\nWASHINGTON. Aug. 29.\u2014Presi\ndent Hoover's selection of Thomas\nWalker Page, a Virginia Democrat,\nas second member of the reorga\nnized tariff commission today\naroused keener interest in the rest\nof personnel of this body, which\nwill be charged with making im\nprovements in the protective sys\ntem set up in the Hawley-Smoot\nbill.\nIn view of Page\u2019s reputed low\ntariff views, which once led him to\ndeclare the Fordney-McCumber rates\ntoo high, even for a protection pro\ngram, as well as his interest in in\nternational attempts to allay com\nmercial rivalries, it was believed the\nPresident yet may choose a com\nmission with more concern for for\neign trade expansion than the Re\npublican party showed in framing\nhigh duties.\nAlthough appointment of Henry\nP. Fletcher of Pennsylvania as\nchairman has brought criticism that\nhe naturally would look with favor\non keeping rates high, Hoover has\nemphasized that the former diplo\nmat\u2019s experience abroad would lead\nhim to take a broad view of applica\ntions for downward revision.\nPage was a member of the first\ntariff board set up by Taft, a\nstaunch advocate of scientific re\nvision, although he could not get\nhis party to follow him. Page sub\nsequently was named as a member\nof the tariff commission by Wilson.\nIn his books and statements he has\nshown himself to be far from the\ntype that the Watson-Smoot-Reed\nbloc would place on the tribunal.\nPage's appointment may lead\nDemocrats and other critics of the\nHawley-Smoot rates to withhold\ntheir attack until the full personnel\nlms been named. There are still\nfour members to be selected, in\ncluding two Democrats and two\nRepublicans, and Hoover has until\nSept. 17 to find them.\nINDIA RULER GIVEN\nLONG PRISON TERM\nTribal Chief Convicted of Hiding\nWeapons, Confining Youth.\nBa United Pirns\nKARASHI, India, Aug. 29.\u2014The\npir of Pagaro, who was convicted at\nSukhar recently of possessing arms\nwithout a license and with wrong\nfully confining a youth at his pal\nace, was sentenced today to ten\nyears imprisonment and 2,000 ru\npees fine.\nWhen the tribal chieftain's pal\nace was raided several months ago\nBritish officials found a big store\nof arms in the cellar, as well as\ncontraband liquor.\nAt the pir's trial he was accused\nby his wives of beating them and\nmaking them work in the fields un\ntil they were exhausted.\nHIGH HONOR IS PAID\nCHANEY AT FUNERAL\nScreen\u2019s Greatest character Actor\nBuried Beside His Father.\nLOS ANGELES, Cal.. Aug. 29.\nLon Chaney, the screen's greatest\nckarecter actor, rested beside his\nfather in Forest Lawn cemetery to\nday as Hollywood resumed its work\nof motion picture making which was\ninterrupted during his last rites.\nChaney's funeral and bnrial late\nThursday called for honors given\nfew celebrities. Representatives of\nthe United States marine corps, of\nwhich he was an honorary member,\nhad charge of the services.\nPerhaps the most impressive part\nof the services occurred in a tiny,\nflower-filled chapel where two mu\nsician friends of Chaney played his\nfavorite song, 'Laugh, Clown,\nLaugh Mrs. Chaney became hy\nsterical when she heard her hus\nbands favorite selection.\nCRIME FROM \u2018THRILLER\u2019\nYouths at Mode See Film Version,\nThen Rob Theater Manager.\nWASHINGTON, Aug. 29,-While\na crime thriller, \u201cThe Shadow of\nthe Law,\u201d was being shown on the\nscreen, two well-dressed youths in\nthe audience arose and started out\nof the Avalon theater here.\nA few moments later, they robbed\nthe theater manager of $265 after\nbinding him in his office.\nWOUNDED IN TONG WAR\nYoung Chinese Almost Hacked to\nDeath; Skull Fractured.\nBu United Prett\nNEW YORK, Aug. 29\u2014A well\ndressed young Chinese was found\ntoday in a lonely section of the\nBronx almost hacked to death. Po\nlice said he was a victim of a rival\ntong.\nThere were at least sixteen gashes\nin lue body and his skull was frac-\nLittle hope Is held for his\nytci?er\u00a3,\nHARRY E. VOSHELL\nChief Indianapolis\nFire Department\n0\nIndianapolis Is an\nUp-and-Coming City\n\u2014a Guarantee of\nProsperity\nPRACTICAL NURSING\n20 Years\u2019 Experience\nDoctors\u2019 and Customers\u2019 rec\nommendation; will leave city.\nCancer Cases Taken\nLILLIAN SPRECHER\n219 Harris St. BE. 0946-M\nNU BONE\nSensationally smart support, excellent\nabdominal and diaphragm control and\nreal comfort, with the famous Nu Bone\nwoven wire stay. Bends edgewise as\nfreely 3R flat wise. Guaranteed against\nrust or breakage. Services in the priv\naey of your home when desired. Open\nings for 23 refined women wlfb or -with\nout sales experience. Training free.\nCall or write\nNU BONE NU TREND\nSHOPPE\n510 State Life Bldg. KUey 9355\nClara Duckum\nDistrict Manager\nALFRED HOUSTON\nState Fire Marshal\nMY SINCERE DESIRE IS TO\nDO MY BEST FOR PROSPER\nITY'S SAKE.\nRue Beauty Shoppe\nPermanent waves, $5 and $7.\nAll lines beauty work.\nIRENE RUGH\n526 N. La Salle CH. 6349\nBRUCE\u2019S TEAROOM\n737 N. Tenn. St.\nBRUCE\u2019S CAFE NO. 2\n235 N. Illinois St.\nSpecial Steak and Chop Dinners, 75c\nSpecial Sunday Dinner, 50c and 75c\nSpecial Business Men's Lunch\nCold Lunch. 40c\nClean, Cool and Appetizing\nSurroundings\nOs course prosperity is ahead\nCAPTAIN C. J. RILEY\nEngine House No. 32\nW. J. VON BERG\nGrocer\n1330 Brookside Ave. CHerry 2921\nJ. W. FINNERAN\nGrocery\n440* S. West St.\nRiley 0474\nSave\u2014Buy Your Coal Now\nHigh Grade Coal\u2014All Price* at\nTUEXDO COAL CO., Inc.\n333S E. New York CHe